> A recipe for enchiladas appeared in Mexico's first ever cookbook, which was published way back in 1831! This is our version of the traditional favourite. Mashing up the beans gives a creamy consistency that we think you'll love. Arriba!

Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C. Put a splash of @olive oil{1%splash} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the @British beef mince{250%g}. Cook until well browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced into half moons). Add to the pan with the browned beef. Cook until soft, ~{6%minutes}. Drain and thoroughly rinse the @red kidney beans{1/2%can} in a #colander{}. Put them in a #mixing bowl{} and mash with a #potato masher{} or fork. Once the onion is soft, add the @Mexican spice{1%packet}. Cook for ~{1%minute} more.

> TIP: Some like it hot, but if you're not one of them, just use a bit less spice.

Add the beans to your pan along with the @tomato passata{1%carton} and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Refill the passata carton(s) one fifth with water, swirl it around and add this too. Let the mixture simmer gently on low heat until it has reduced by half and is lovely and thick. Meanwhile, roughly slice the @baby gem lettuce{1}(roughly sliced) and chop the @vine tomatoes{2}(chopped).

Once the mixture is thick, take it off the heat. Spoon equal amounts down one side of each @super soft tortillas with whole wheat{4}. Roll the tortillas up into cylinders and place them in an #ovenproof dish{}. Pack them snugly, side by side, with the folded edge downwards so they don't unroll. Grate over the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}. Place on the top shelf of your oven and bake until the cheese melts.

Whilst the enchiladas are in your oven, pop the @sour cream{1} in a #small bowl{}. Grate in the @lime{1/2}(zested) and add a few good grinds of @black pepper{a few good grinds}. Mix well.

In another mixing bowl, toss the baby gem lettuce and tomato with a squeeze of @lime juice{squeeze} and the @olive oil{1%tbsp}. Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a few good grinds of black pepper.

Serve the enchiladas with a dollop of zesty sour cream and the salad on the side. Devour immediately!